choices.text:
that school ends far too early! (I know I'm probably annoying, been thinking about going back for years, but I need some push) But! My parents did instill a work ethic in me and my siblings. My entire family, including me will go to work six days a week without complaint (and we'll be happy it's not 7 days a week). I went to work as soon as I got old enough and never felt like I was wasting my life. That being said: I don't get paid enough to be working my butt off for each client who type speedy messages on their phone.
I currently work in a call center lost my job because they found out I was a LGBTQ+. They still wont tell me what I did wrong even though  
claiming that just because I was not accepted by my parents is not a reason to retaliate etc. (not in those words but that's what they mean). I want to work there again but I need to either find same people to report above them or a top worker to report above them. I love working their product but it's very hard to right the wrong across all of the markets.
For me I'm glad when school is over but I hate looking for a job. My biggest problem is there needs to be less paperwork! At least in Canada, it doesn't need to be so much forms to fill out to find out if they're hiring!
